data.OTHER_INFORMATION: The killer whale stranded on the Netherlands coast and taken to Hardewijk Dolphinarium for treatment. DNA was extracted to identify population of origin, which together with family-specific vocal dialects identified the killer whale as originating from the population that feeds upon and follows the Norwegian spring-spawning herring stock. The killer whale, named Morgan, is now housed at Lorro Parque, Tenerife.
